16:46.939 --> 16:48.975
Also, the new card
would've bounced

16:49.008 --> 16:51.010
on account of we're broke.

16:51.044 --> 16:53.680
So I guess I'm worthless,
dead or alive.

16:55.615 --> 16:57.584
You're worth something to me.

16:59.352 --> 17:01.088
I'm so pathetic.

17:01.121 --> 17:02.722
Being pregnant is the only time

17:02.755 --> 17:04.457
I've ever really felt special.

17:06.359 --> 17:08.428
I mean, since I stopped
playing Clarissa

17:08.461 --> 17:09.829
on the Nickelodeon cruise.

17:09.862 --> 17:11.431
You're always special.

17:11.464 --> 17:13.100
Even when you're being
a huge bitch.

17:13.133 --> 17:14.834
Aw.

17:14.867 --> 17:16.436
Remember before
when you said that thing

17:16.469 --> 17:18.338
about only wanting
to get knocked up

17:18.371 --> 17:19.672
because it made you
feel special?

17:19.706 --> 17:22.675
Well, if we're keeping it 100...

17:22.709 --> 17:24.744
I was stalling.

17:24.777 --> 17:27.680
Yeah, at first just for
the money, but then I realized

17:27.714 --> 17:31.184
the idea of you being preggers
with someone else's kiddo

17:31.218 --> 17:33.186
kind of made me feel...

17:33.220 --> 17:36.223
like not a man or whatnot.

17:37.257 --> 17:40.227
Anyjunk, feelings are stupid.

17:40.260 --> 17:44.197
Vernon, the fact that you were
even open to the idea

17:44.231 --> 17:46.799
in the first place
just shows how confident

17:46.833 --> 17:49.436
-and secure you are.
-(children laughing)

17:49.469 --> 17:51.037
And that's really sexy.

17:51.070 --> 17:53.240
Sexy, huh?

17:53.273 --> 17:55.408
-Very.
-GIRL: Here.

17:57.510 --> 17:59.746
Aw.

17:59.779 --> 18:02.048
Things are gonna get better
for us, just you wait.

18:02.081 --> 18:04.717
Once I get funding for
my Korean medical food truck,

18:04.751 --> 18:07.620
everything's gonna be
coming up Vernon. And Becca.

18:09.356 --> 18:11.057
And Tallulah. Shit.

18:11.090 --> 18:15.328
Well, I believe in you, honey.

18:15.362 --> 18:19.632
I mean, I have to.

18:19.666 --> 18:22.735
-(laughs)
-Ow!

18:22.769 --> 18:25.405
-Shitballs.
-Oh! Aw.

18:25.438 --> 18:27.840
Poor baby. Here.

18:29.842 --> 18:31.978
One hour to the eclipse!
I repeat,

18:32.011 --> 18:33.513
one hour to the ecl...

18:41.388 --> 18:44.757
Ladies and gentlemen, boys
and girls, this is the moment

18:44.791 --> 18:46.826
we've all been waiting for.
Are you ready?

18:46.859 --> 18:48.761
-CROWD: Yes!
-Well, then,

18:48.795 --> 18:50.096
look to the skies!

18:55.168 --> 18:56.569
(giggles)

19:00.807 --> 19:04.010
It's so neat.

19:04.043 --> 19:06.246
(indistinct chatter)

19:16.523 --> 19:19.359
(crowd cheering)

19:20.393 --> 19:22.229
GILMARTIN:
Yes!

19:23.930 --> 19:27.967
Brilliant! Brilliant!

19:28.000 --> 19:30.203
Absolutely brilliant.

19:30.237 --> 19:32.239
Ah, wonderful.

19:46.052 --> 19:48.821
GILMARTIN:
Eclipses never fail

19:48.855 --> 19:51.190
to cast their magic spells,
do they?

19:51.224 --> 19:53.826
-Indeed, they do not.
-(both chuckle)

19:53.860 --> 19:55.094
Please, have a seat.

19:57.797 --> 19:59.732
Did your guests
enjoy themselves?

19:59.766 --> 20:03.536
I think so. It's complicated.

20:03.570 --> 20:07.173
Oh, must be nice to have family.

20:07.206 --> 20:10.377
It's always just been me
and the cosmos.

20:10.410 --> 20:12.579
And the prostitutes.

20:12.612 --> 20:14.080
Well...

20:14.113 --> 20:16.516
I've come to understand
that the main attraction

20:16.549 --> 20:20.620
of having Becca as my surrogate
was so, in some small way,

20:20.653 --> 20:24.557
my marriage wouldn't have been
a total waste.

20:24.591 --> 20:27.294
Well, there is no waste
in the universe.

20:27.327 --> 20:31.364
When something comes to an end,
be it a galactic age,

20:31.398 --> 20:34.801
a star or a weekend away,

20:34.834 --> 20:38.638
it is simultaneously
the beginning of something else.

20:38.671 --> 20:42.875
Loss can be hard, but you might
be mourning something

20:42.909 --> 20:45.912
that was never actually there
in the first place.

20:45.945 --> 20:49.816
Yes, maybe this idea you had
of making a new family

20:49.849 --> 20:52.051
slipped through your fingers,

20:52.084 --> 20:55.388
but perhaps there's
something else already there

20:55.422 --> 20:57.424
that you've failed to see.

21:06.833 --> 21:08.835
(spits)

